Comment_glosser: According to the contributor, in Western Parbate Kham, Takale dialect has only numerals 'one' to 'three' of Tibeto-Burman origin, while Maikoti dialect has numerals 'one' to 'five', higher numerals are borrowed from Nepali.
There is a very high level of allomorphy in components meaning ‘10’; some prime symbols are used, but they do not cover the extent of the variation
